Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal, and in particular Article 89 (1) thereof,
Having regard to Council Regulation No 136/66/EEC of 22 September 1966 on the establishment of a common organization of the market in oils and fats (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1720/91 (3), and in particular Article 22 (4) and Article 24a  (2) thereof,
Having regard to the proposal from the Commission (4),
Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament (5),
Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (6),
Whereas, when the target prices and intervention prices for rape and sunflower seed are fixed, account should be taken of the objectives of the common agricultural policy;
Whereas the intervention price must be fixed in accordance with the criteria laid down in Article 24 (1) of Regulation No 136/66/EEC;
Whereas the prices of rape and sunflower seed must be fixed for specific standard qualities;
Whereas the supplement to be applied to the target price, to the intervention price and to the intervention buying-in price for 'double zero' rape seed must be fixed in accordance with the criteria laid down in Article 24a of Regulation No 136/66/EEC;
